State-run Iranian groups signed
contracts valued at $1.3 billion to develop the Tusan, Alfa and
Band-e-Karkheh oil fields, the Oil Ministryâ€™s news website Shana
 reported .  Petroleum Engineering and Development Co., an affiliate of
the National Iranian Oil Co., agreed yesterday with a state-
owned  investment company  to develop the Band-e-Karkheh field,
which is estimated to hold 4 billion barrels of crude, according
to the report.  Iranian Offshore Oil Co. signed a contract for Tusan,
estimated to hold 400 million barrels of in-place crude
reserves, and Alfa, which has a capacity to produce as much as
to 10,000 barrels a day of crude, Shana reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
